@markstory But, for example, the following code will cause a fatal error if people are not using `EntityTrait` to implement their own `EntityInterface` classes, as `EntityInterface` doesn't have the method:
https://github.com/cakephp/cakephp/blob/94f7011941e81226943c368545372818c1bc96ce/src/ORM/Table.php#L1721
And if people are using `EntityTrait`, then no fatal errors occur even if we change the `EntityInterface`.

@inoas Strictly speaking, there are no ignorable errors, as I said above. I think @ADmad also has explained the same thing above.
